Artificer

Artificer is not currently available for player selection. The class is under
wizard testing and the Brass Crucible route and attunement rite are disabled.

Artificer is a remort class, not a guild. Its membership and GXP survive
future remorts even though level, stats, and guilds reset normally.

An Artificer's Cinis Engine replaces the ordinary corpse burner. It retains
burn corpse, burn all corpse, check burner, and cinis while also storing class
status, ash, essence, prototypes, and active workings.

Commands:
  artificer
  crucible
  artificer abilities
  artificer progression
  artificer study <body|soul|confluence>
  resonate <item|living>
  bellowsblow [foe]
  temper <equipment> with <cinder|ichor|confluence>
  bulwark
  awaken <carried weapon>
  fabricate aether mount
  artifice <primary unique armour> with <carried unique armour>
  prototype <coil|ward|starburst>
  deploy <coil [foe]|ward|starburst>
  unmake [number|all]

Bosses yield cinder when their physical nature dominates and ichor when their
mental or spiritual nature dominates. Boss tier controls the amount. Harvests,
tempering, and inventions award permanent Artificer GXP.

Permanent Artificer GXP determines rank and available Load. Mastery uses the
same cumulative GXP with diminishing returns. It is roughly 90 percent at 31,500 GXP,
94 percent at 60,000, and 99 percent at 350,000. It strengthens bounded parts
of class abilities but never replaces current level and stats.

Body costs five cinder per rank. Soul costs five ichor. Confluence requires at
least one rank in each and costs three of each. Discipline ranks cap at five.

Prepared inventions persist through logout and remort. Coil requires Soul 1,
ward requires Body 1, and starburst requires Confluence 1. Prototype slots grow
slowly with permanent mastery.

Chimera armour opens at Confluence 2 and 50 percent mastery. It costs ten
cinder and ten ichor to fold part of one carried unique armour into a worn
or carried unique using exactly the same non-accessory slots. Each seam uses
2 Load and reserves 5 percent maximum HP and 8 percent maximum SP. The donor
remains reserved at full carried weight. Removing the primary suspends its
benefits; the seam ends on expiry or unmaking. Higher GXP permits multiple
seams, to a hard cap of three. Unique scripts are never copied. Confluence 3
also echoes the donor's strongest positive resistance.

Portable Bulwark opens at rank 3 and Body 2. It spends grey ash and reserves
4 percent HP, 4 percent SP, and one Load. Awaken Weapon opens at rank 4 with
Body 2 and Soul 2; it reserves a real non-unique weapon inside a temporary
combat construct and returns it when the working ends. At rank 5 and Soul 3,
Fabricate creates a persistent shoulder implant whose automatic aether shot
consumes SP and blue ash.
